<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>13682</anchor> <rss>jms-0069.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Table</taxon> <addr>jms-0069</addr>  <route>jms-0069.xml</route>   <title>Transclusion options in <link href="jms-005V.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.2">Forester 2.2</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><table>    <tr>    <th>Fluid Binding</th>    <th>Default</th>    <th>Meaning</th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/title</code></td>    <td><em>(none)</em></td>    <td>To override the tree's title during transclusion.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/toc</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Show the tree in the table of contents.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/expanded</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Whether the tree is expanded or not.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/heading</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>If set to <code>false</code>, the tree's contents will be inlined.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/metadata</code></td>    <td><code>false</code></td>    <td>Show in a tree's heading.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/numbered</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Whether the tree is displayed with a number or not, transitively on subtrees.</td>  </tr></table><p>It is possible to achieve undesirable results by combining these options in undesirable ways; it is up to you to use them correctly.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>13683</anchor> <rss>jms-0067.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0067</addr>  <route>jms-0067.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Flexible transclusion options in <link href="jms-005V.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.2">Forester 2.2</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>This release replaces the old <code>\transclude*</code>, <code>\transclude@</code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <link href="jms-005O.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.1">Forester 2.1</link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</p><pre>\transclude{jms-0005}</pre><p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <link href="jms-0069.xml" type="local" title="Transclusion options in Forester 2.2">table below</link>.</p>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>13684</anchor> <rss>jms-0069.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Table</taxon> <addr>jms-0069</addr>  <route>jms-0069.xml</route>   <title>Transclusion options</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><table>    <tr>    <th>Fluid Binding</th>    <th>Default</th>    <th>Meaning</th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/title</code></td>    <td><em>(none)</em></td>    <td>To override the tree's title during transclusion.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/toc</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Show the tree in the table of contents.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/expanded</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Whether the tree is expanded or not.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/heading</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>If set to <code>false</code>, the tree's contents will be inlined.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/metadata</code></td>    <td><code>false</code></td>    <td>Show in a tree's heading.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/numbered</code></td>    <td><code>true</code></td>    <td>Whether the tree is displayed with a number or not, transitively on subtrees.</td>  </tr></table><p>It is possible to achieve undesirable results by combining these options in undesirable ways; it is up to you to use them correctly.</p></mainmatter> </tree>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>13685</anchor> <rss>jms-0068.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Example</taxon> <addr>jms-0068</addr>  <route>jms-0068.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>A configured transclusion</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The following code produces an unnumbered transclusion that nonetheless appears in the table of context, with an overridden title.</p><pre>\scope{
  \put\transclude/title{A short title in context}
  \put\transclude\numbered{false}
  \transclude{jms-0068}
}
</pre></mainmatter> </tree>  
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>13686</anchor> <rss>jms-005V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Changelog</taxon> <addr>jms-005V</addr>  <route>jms-005V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Forester 2.2</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>13687</anchor> <rss>jms-0067.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0067</addr>  <route>jms-0067.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Flexible transclusion options</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>This release replaces the old <code>\transclude*</code>, <code>\transclude@</code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <link href="jms-005O.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.1">Forester 2.1</link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</p><pre>\transclude{jms-0005}</pre><p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <link href="jms-0069.xml" type="local" title="Transclusion options in Forester 2.2">table below</link>.</p>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb> <crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>13688</anchor> <rss>jms-0069.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Table</taxon> <addr>jms-0069</addr>  <route>jms-0069.xml</route>   <title>Transclusion options</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><table>    <tr>    <th>Fluid Binding</th>    