</mainmatter> </tree>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>13690</anchor> <rss>jms-0066.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0066</addr>  <route>jms-0066.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Query nodes</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>This release adds support for generating subsections from transclusions obtained by a query the forest; this can be used to produce topical bibliographies.</p>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb> <crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>13691</anchor> <rss>jms-006A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Example</taxon> <addr>jms-006A</addr>  <route>jms-006A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>A conjunctive query node</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The following code will generate a subsection entitled “featured talks” containing the appropriate items as collapsed subtrees:</p><pre>\scope{
  \put\transclude/title{featured talks}
  \query{
    \query/and{
      \query/author{jonmsterling}
      \query/taxon{reference}
      \query/tag{featured}
    }
  }
}</pre><p>Under the hood, a query node is an “anonymous transclusion” and can therefore be <link href="jms-0067.xml" type="local" title="Flexible transclusion options in Forester 2.2">configured using the same options as other transclusions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree>  
<p>A minor change is that the <code>assets</code> directly does not need to be flat anymore.</p><p>As always, existing forests can be upgraded by copying <code>forest.xsl</code> and <code>style.css</code> into their <code>assets</code> directory. </p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>13692</anchor> <rss>jms-0067.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Feature</taxon> <addr>jms-0067</addr>  <route>jms-0067.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Flexible transclusion options in <link href="jms-005V.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.2">Forester 2.2</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>This release replaces the old <code>\transclude*</code>, <code>\transclude@</code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <link href="jms-005O.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.1">Forester 2.1</link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</p><pre>\transclude{jms-0005}</pre><p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <link href="jms-0069.xml" type="local" title="Transclusion options in Forester 2.2">table below</link>.</p>    <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>13693</anchor> <rss>jms-0069.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Table</taxon> <addr>jms-0069</addr>  <route>jms-0069.xml</route>   <title>Transclusion options</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><table>    <tr>    <th>Fluid Binding</th>    <th>Default</th>    <th>Meaning</th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><code>\transclude/title</code></td>    <td><em>(none)</em></td>    <td>To override the tree's title durin